For the first time ever, non-priests could

00:07:20.300 --> 00:07:25.559
read the Bible for themselves, because Luther
used the German that people actually spoke,

00:07:25.559 --> 00:07:28.779
instead of Latin, and his work quickly caught
on among common people.

00:07:28.780 --> 00:07:32.860
Hundreds of thousands of copies of Luther’s
Bible were printed; people carried it in their

00:07:32.860 --> 00:07:37.539
pockets and memorized it. Now everyone could
quote scripture and discuss its meaning.

00:07:37.539 --> 00:07:41.259
Now, Luther’s theory was that if everyone
